subSubSection.paragraph:
Body oval, moderately convex, dorsum with pale yellow pubescence (
Figs 10a–i
). Head black with slightly yellowish brown near labrum or all black (
Figs 10c, 10f
), antennae and mouthparts yellowish brown, tip of mandibles dark brown. Pronotum yellowish brown with a black or dark brown longitudinal stripe at middle (
Figs 10c, 10f, 10i
). Scutellar shield black. Elytra black (
Figs 10a–f
). Prothoracic hypomeron and prosternum brown. Mesoventrite and elytral epipleurae dark brown, metaventrite black. Legs yellowish brown.

Head with fine frontal punctures, as large as eye facets, 0.5–1.0 diameters apart. Eye densely faceted, interocular distance about 0.33 times of head width (
Figs 10c, 10f
). Pronotal punctures slightly larger than those on frons, 1.0–1.5 diameters apart. Surface of elytra with punctures much larger than those on pronotum, separated by 1.0–2.0 diameters.

Abdominal postcoxal lines complete and moderately recurved, reaching 4/5 length of ventrite 1 (
Fig. 10j
), area enclosed by the lines finely and sparsely punctate, irregularly distributed, broadly smooth along the lines; ventrite 1 with coarse and sparse punctures at middle.

Male genitalia. Penis short and slender, slightly broadened at base, apex pointed (
Fig. 10k
); tegmen with penis guide subtriangular, widest at base, gradually tapering to apex in lateral view (
Fig. 10l
), slightly longer than 2/3 length of parameres; penis guide in inner view subtriangular, widest at base, narrowing to apex (

Fig. 
10m

); parameres stout and elongate oval with few setae at apex in lateral view (
Fig. 10l
).
